  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the time taken by Bus A to overtake Bus B when travelling in the same direction</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
Two buses are traveling on the same road in the same direction. Bus A moves at {@vA@} km/h, and Bus B moves at {@vB@} km/h. At a certain moment, Bus A is {@d_val@} {@d_unit@} behind Bus B.
</p>
<p>How long will it take for Bus A to overtake Bus B?</p>
<p>Time \(=\) [[input:ans1]] hours [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>Since both buses travel in the same direction, Bus A approaches Bus B at the
<strong>relative speed</strong>:</p>
<p>\( {@vA@} - {@vB@} = {@v_rel@} \text{ km/h}\)</p>
<p>The initial distance between the buses is:
\({@d_km@} \text{ km}\)</p>
<p>The time needed to overtake is: <br>
\(\begin{align} t =& \frac{\text{distance}}{\text{relative speed}}\\
=& \frac{{@d_km@}}{{@v_rel@}}\\
=& {@ta@} \text{ hours} \end{align}\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
    <defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
    <penalty>0.1</penalty>
    <hidden>0</hidden>
